                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15341036" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 04:13:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;felixcheung&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13798&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13798&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15341126" author="felixcheung" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 05:29:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not clear what should be the right behavior but `sparkR.init()` deprecated.&lt;br/&gt;
We could either&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Deprecate this&lt;br/&gt;
2) Deprecate this and add proper support for its replacement, if any, from SparkSession&lt;br/&gt;
3) Add official API for getting SparkContext from the SparkSession.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=shivaram&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;shivaram&quot;&gt;shivaram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15341142" author="shivaram" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 05:41:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why don&apos;t we convert these also to the form where we use the implicit SparkContext (similar to setLogLevel) ? Is the concern that these functions are not useful anywhere in SparkR ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15341263" author="felixcheung" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 07:09:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s possible - both setLogLevel and spark.lapply are new in 2.0.0, so it&apos;s very easy just to remove the sc parameter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These have been around so should we simply remove the sc parameter from the signature? These are S3 methods so it could break people. To make it back compatible we would code to check parameter type and so on, similar to sqlContext methods we did in 2.0.0 except we would need a bunch of new code for sc instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15342269" author="shivaram" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 17:35:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah this is a good question - The one thing I&apos;m trying to see is if job groups are useful for naming and canceling jobs run on DataFrames as well. If so I think we should retain this functionality either through SparkSession or by doing the parameter type patching etc. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rxin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rxin&quot;&gt;rxin&lt;/a&gt; Any idea how frequently setJobGroup and cancelJobGroup are used in practice ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15342335" author="rxin" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 18:04:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yea actually it&apos;s used by Databricks (and possibly other platforms)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15342400" author="falaki" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 18:32:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for keeping the API in 2.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15342411" author="shivaram" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 18:35:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In that case lets do the parameter patching thing where we have a version which works without the `sc` arg and with it for backwards compatibility. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=felixcheung&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;felixcheung&quot;&gt;felixcheung&lt;/a&gt; I dont think we need another general purpose mechanism like the one we have in DataFrame.R &amp;#8211; we can just patch these 3 functions explicitly if this is a one-time thing ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15343807" author="felixcheung" created="Wed, 22 Jun 2016 06:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right, since they are S3 methods there really isn&apos;t any function overloading here. A big part of the work is going to be inspecting the class of the first parameter and then patch up the call. Also tricking roxygen2 to generate doc for the right parameter list.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m testing the fix now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15343856" author="apachespark" created="Wed, 22 Jun 2016 07:45:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;felixcheung&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13838&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13838&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15346729" author="shivaram" created="Thu, 23 Jun 2016 16:45:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 13838&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13838&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13838&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
